FT  29 MAY 92 / World Commodities Prices: Fruit &amp; vegetables
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Imported cherries are superb this week at Dollars 1.20-2.00 a lb (Dollars
1.20-2.60) reports the FFVIB. Other good buys include Cape Granny Smith
apples at 55-60p a lb (45-55p) Spania apricots at 70-90p a lb (Pounds
2.00-2.20) and South American Mangoes at 85p-Pounds 1.00 each (85p-Pounds
1.00). English new potatoes at 15-20p a lb (20-30p) are this week's best
vegetable choice. Flat mushrooms at 60-70p a  1/2 (60-70p) and cup mushrooms
at 50-70p a  1/2 (50-70p) along with French courgettes at 50-70p a lb
(65-75p) round up the best vegetable buys. British tomatoes at 65-75p a lb
(80-90p) along with the beef variety at 70-85p a lb (80-90p) are excellent
this week.
