<TEXT>
EQUITABLE Life Assurance, one of the largest US insurance companies,
reported an after-tax loss of Dollars 13m during the first quarter of 1992,
compared with a loss of Dollars 14.6m in the same period a year earlier,
according to filings with the Securities and Exchange Commission.
