FT  29 MAY 92 / UK Company News: Falling car sales put brake on Caffyns
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Falling sales of new cars and losses at four showrooms reduced Caffyns, the
Sussex-based motor group, to little more than break-even last year.
Pre-tax profit fell from Pounds 711,000 to Pounds 63,000 on sales of Pounds
