</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
The European Bank for Reconstruction and Development (EBRD) has agreed a
strategy for Russia which will concentrate on funding financial sector
reform, privatisation, the conversion of military industry, energy projects
and agro-business, writes Anthony Robinson, East Europe Editor.
Mr Jacques Attali, EBRD president, told a European Community-organised aid
conference in Lisbon last week that the bank was authorised to devote up to
40 per cent of its resources to projects in the former Soviet states and up
to Ecu4bn (Dollars 4.96bn) of its own funds to projects in Russia and the
other republics over the next three years.
