sought by Freeman is a balancing item. Although indemnified by Manpower for
the DTI inquiries as a condition of his resignation in 1989, Mr Berry says
he has yet to be reimbursed for any of the legal fees incurred.
Mr Mitchell Fromstein, Manpower's chairman, said the company's decision on
how much and when to pay Mr Berry depended on the outcome of the still
unpublished second report. He believed the company had met Mr Berry's legal
fees from the first inquiry.
