FT  28 MAY 92 / World Commodities Prices: Wool
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Australian wool prices are holding firm after a brief spell of firming. A
distinction is still drawn between better and more stylish wools and the
less reliable types, and it is clear that buyers remain very selective.
There has been a continuing and for important sectors of the wool-consuming
industry a worrying lull in new business, following a widely-experienced
surge in February. The recession still has its impact especially in the UK,
which the important carpet sector depends on housing sales for good demand
on the domestic side.
